Soap Drive to benefit Black Hills Area Schools at Sweet Clover Salon the rest of the month! ⁣
⁣
We have a percentage of children in our communities who don’t have access to regular showers outside of school. We wanted to fill the school showers with enough hygiene supplies to keep everyone showered and comfortable for as long as possible!⁣
⁣
Bring in any new or slightly used shampoo, conditioner, body wash to the salon or reach out to me to arrange drop off for the remainder of December. ⁣
⁣
Feel free to share! 

#lauradoesmyhair #blackhillssoapdrive #blackhills

Grey Blending 🧑‍🎨 
When my clients aren’t up for the maintenance of a monthly root touch up I love to suggest blending with high and lowlights.

For Petes Sake, turn your flat irons down and use your thermal protection products!!

Here are some tips for healthy hair ⬇️

• Reapply your heat protection products between wash days when you style with heat
• Keep your hot tools under 350 degrees and keep the tool moving continuously when using on your hair 
• Use a deep conditioning treatment once a week to keep the ends of your hair soft and moisturized 
• Use your favorite bond building treatment every few weeks to keep your hair strong
• Remember dry hair is fragile and brittle and will snap off without TLC 
• Maintain regular trims to keep those ends friends 

#lauradoesmyhair #behindthechair #btclaughblast #modernsalon #americansalon #olaplex #k18hair #k18

My favorite blonde bombshell 🌟 

This soft golden blonde is so beautiful and flattering on my client. I love Kenra Studio Stylist Express for my root touch up clients. It processes in 10 min under heat and gives great coverage. It’s perfect for my clients that maintain their color often. 

3 Rows Weft extensions• we alternate between a light summer blonde and darker caramel blonde and apply them together for a perfect custom blend. Seasonally we will swap a weft lighter or darker. 

Styled with Unite 7 seconds detangler, Boosta Spray, Expanda Volume & Elevate Mousse, finished with Texturiza hairspray. This client comes In 2x weekly for a wash & blowout and likes her volume to last.

HERE IS MY SECRET FOR SEAMLESS GROW OUT ⬇️

Babylights create a beautiful blend and look natural for clients who want an overall change without stark or bold color placement. To make that blend last even longer, here is my tip for glossing your client. 

I like to Root tap 1/2 level darker when I gloss to keep babylights soft as it grows out. I have a few favorite demi permanent color lines that I use for different purposes. Some give a stronger coverage, some more translucent. I’ll name drop in the comments 👇🏻

This formula was 08n + 09V on the top 1/2 inch at the root. 
Ends were 010NA + 09 V

Do you have a favorite line to tone your clients or do you use multiple color lines?

❄️Winter Blonde❄️

This is what I like to call my blondes this time of year, when I enhance the depth  in their hair color as it coincides with the coldest, darkest, time of the year in the northern hemisphere. 

The blonde is impactful, placed where it will pop and around the face and at a few key places like around the hairline at the ears and nape. I melted at her root and pulled some through her mid shaft, leaving the ends out to keep it overall blonde.

Copper LOB on my beautiful client @justinechloie 

I like to do a Top Coat of gloss on my red and copper clients. It adds dimension, and extends the life of your reds. Over highlights I apply a gloss at the bowl, 2x . Over permanent color I apply 1 gloss after rinsing. 

I have a few favorite color lines for my reds and coppers (Surface Hy-Demi color and Redken Shades) and love formulating redheads.
